Table 2 and Fig. 2 provide the mean score, standard deviation, and score range achieved for each questionnaire. There were no floor or ceiling effects in the ULFI-PL questionnaire, because the percentage of the lowest or highest scores was less than 15%. Additionally, none of the participants achieved the minimum score on the ULFI-PL assessments, and the maximum score on the ULFI-PL was reached by fewer than 2% of participants in the third assessment only.
